Microsoft is developing the Surface Hub 2 and plans to announce more details about the device before the end of June, The Verge reported. The Surface Hub is Microsoft’s 55-inch and 84-inch smart displays aimed at enterprises. No details about the features of the second-generation Surface Hub were shared, but Microsoft confirmed it is working on an operating system upgrade for existing Surface Hus. Microsoft Teams integration will be available on the Surface Hub in the coming months, the company added.